    {
      q: 'Is the AeroPress Go better than the AeroPress Original for backpacking?',
      a: 'Usually for convenience, yes. Usually for weight, no. The Go is the nicer all-in-one travel kit, while the Original is lighter and gives you a little more brew room if you do not mind building your own setup around it.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Are paper or metal filters better for hiking?',
      a: 'Paper filters are lighter, cleaner, and easier to live with on the trail. Metal filters make a fuller cup and save waste, but they also need a better rinse and can leave more silt in the last sip.',
    },
    {
      q: 'How do you clean an AeroPress while hiking?',
      a: 'The easy version is still the best version: press out the puck, wipe the cap if needed, and give the parts a quick rinse. Paper filters make this almost laughably simple. Metal filters take a little more water and a little more patience.',
