      q: 'Do you need to carry a grinder for hiking coffee?',
      a: 'Not always. If you are on a short trip, good pre-ground coffee is totally fine. A manual grinder makes more sense on longer trips, for fresher beans, or when you care enough about cup quality to carry the extra weight.',
